2 types of hypervisor!
  1) bear metal (installed on hardware)
     No underlying operating system
      Very fast, secure, stable
      Used in data centers, enterprises
Examples : KVM, Xen
  

  2) type 2 (installed on OS )
     Works like normal software
      Slower than Type 1 because it depends on the host OS
      Used for personal, testing, labs
Examples:VirtualBox, VMware Workstation, Parallels Desktop



